    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, p. 113, n. <citedRange>92</citedRange>, fig. 48 </bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.204</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>024800</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, p. <citedRange>204</citedRange></bibl> (date of the base);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>139</citedRange></bibl> (possible provenance);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.84</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65784"><name nymRef="#Τελεσώι">Τελεσὼι</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65706"><name nymRef="#Σωσίας" type="patronymic">Σω<unclear>σ</unclear>ία</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Telesô fille de Sosias.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Teleso daughter of Sosias.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Telesò figlia di Sosias.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Teleso might be sister of Philon (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr024700</ref>): both bases, published together and very similar,
                    should come from the same tomb.</p>
    	   <p>The Thorns' probable attribution to the North Necropolis is due to the fact that the Italian archaeologists before World War II were mainly interested 
    	   in this one.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
